main.description: Manually written Non-Standard Operations (NSO) list used by BICAS (SolO/RPW/BIAS calibration and data processing). Contains "events", i.e. time intervals, each one labelled with a standardized string (NSO ID, or RCS NSO ID) that BICAS can interpret. BICAS uses this list to modify how datasets are processed, e.g. by setting zVariables QUALITY_FLAG and/or L2_QUALITY_BITMASK, replacing data with fill values, and/or omitting data from L3 etc.

notesTable.note: 2020-11-12, Erik P G Johansson: I have not managed to manually find any thruster firings for time period 2020-02-12 to 2020-03-29.
2021-05-24, Erik P G Johansson: Data has not been systematically searched for saturation, but should cover most cases (or at least the most egregious ones) up until 2021-03-06.
2023-12-13, Erik P G Johansson: Table should contain all thruster firings for the time period 2020-02-12 (launch+2 days) to 2023-12-10 (inclusive). Only contains manually identified thuster firings.

Note that since data gaps may be filled in after that a time interval has been manually searched for thruster firings etc., this list still might not label all such thruster firings (etc.) in the time period(s) that has/have been stated to be searched.
